div.p: SANDEL, or Sundana, Island, in the Eastern Seas, about eighty miles in length, and from fifteen to thirty-six in breadth. Long. 119. 33. to 120. E. Lat. 9. 35. to 10. 15. S.
S ANDELWOOD Isle, an island in the Eastern Seas, a hundred miles in length by thirty in average breadth. It is situated to the south of the island of Flores, about the tenth degree of north latitude.
